snippet.title: "Super Flipper" (1975) arcade video pinball gameplay.
snippet.description:
"Super Flipper" was the first video pinball game. Released by Chicago Coin in 1975. It use transistor circuits and has no memory or CPU.

Shown here played at the Northwest Pinball and Arcade Show in Tacoma, Washington on 6/4/2016.
